<disease>
    <name>Mevalonate Kinase Deficiency</name>
    <descriptions>Autosomal recessive disorder caused by mutations in the mevalonate kinase gene. Because of the mutations cholesterol biosynthesis is disrupted and mevalonic acid accumulates. It is characterized by a range of symptoms, including dysmorphic facies, psychomotor retardation, cataract, hepatosplenomegaly, cerebellar ataxia, elevated immunoglobulin D, and recurrent febrile crises with fever; lymphadenopathy; arthralgia; edema; and rash.</descriptions>
